node.text: Lately @sick_bunny_o_o turned me into a lolita and I felt like a totally different person! When I was 13 or something I really wanted to be part of gothic lolita culture but back then I couldn’t afford expensive fancy dresses and aliexpress shipping was not a thing back then (I’m from a small town and we had no local alternative clothing stores). Also I’ve never had a soft, childish, doll-like appearance so I’ve felt that this style does not  suit me… But it was such fun when Bunny picked an outfit for me! She even promised that she’ll complete a full gothic-lolita costume for me! 🖤 do you have any child/teenage dreams that were out of your reach back then but now you fulfilled them as an adult? #lolitafashion #brolita

node.text:
Still recharging my batteries but I managed to sketch Antek in some fancy clothes <3 // Last days were busy, I was moving from my recent tattoo shop to a new place. Painting furnitures with friends, trying to arrange new space… that’s a start of a new adventure, but I’ll tell you about it another time! 🌿 I’m still kinda homeless because renovations in soon-to-be-my-new-flat are delayed AGAIN. But thanks to my kind friends me, Gabe and cats can stay in their tiny house for the time of need. I’m grateful but as far as I love having these good souls around me, I won’t lie - I miss having my own, private space. Normaly I need quite a lot of me-time. A space and time only for myself to recharge my batteries and create. I’m used to having lot of space - I always had my own room in my parent’s house, I only had to share a room during my uni years, but it was a short period of time. Maybe people who got used to share a room with siblings/parents/roommates are more used to couch surfing livestyle? Being easily content with just a roof over their head and a wamr place to sleep, having people around, not needing much privacy? (Share your opinion if you want to!)
.
I’m trying to not think that I’m a burden to my friends, but I know that we all can’t wait to regain our own spaces. I guess it’s a very introvert thing? Having this deep need for a place only for ourselves. I so want to finally be able to furnish and decor my very own nest! A nest for me, Gabe and our kitty girls 🐱 Soon. Hopefully soon 🌿

node.text:
Happy #pridemonth guyz! Show me your colors in comments. My colors are:
🟡⚪️🟣⚫️ + 💖💜💙
.
So here’s the rare picture of me with my male persona Yanek. I struggled with my gender identity a lot, I’m a female but very far away from calling myself a cis person. I wish I could be just an unisex being, free of the feeling like I have to fit in some canons to be accepted. I like my both femine and masculine sides and usually I feel the most comfortable being just somewhere in between. I finally started to like and embrace my androgynous look. It took me a long time to accept myself as I am instead of fighting against my head and struggling with the constant feeling that I have to fit in some canons or else don’t belong. So I guess it’s my official comming out post, that I identify myself as a non-binary person 🌸 as well as bisexual, but you probably already know about that.
🌸
You often ask for my pronouns - in daily life I use she/her but I’m comfortable with any forms, he/him and they/them are fine as well.
🌸
As for Yanek - most of you already know that he’s my male-persona, created partly to fulfill my fantasies about being a man and partly because I didn’t felt comfortable with portraing myself as a woman. He’s a cis guy, also bi-sexual 🌸
.
I’m happy to say that at this moment I’m getting more and more comfortable with myself. It’s a good feeling after all these years of struggling with my identity 🌸
.
#pride2021 #pride #nonbinary #bisexual #bisexualpride #nonbinarypride

node.text:
// POWER SAVING MODE : ON //
As you might have noticed I’m not much active recently. There is lot of important matters in my not-online life I have to take care for and they just consume my whole energy, leaving me with just enough to somewhow keep going forward. It’s not the best time for my creativity, not the best time to take a break and relax, important shit has to be done first. Just thinking about chatting with people or creating new stuff for my instagram makes me even more tired. Hiding in my shell, ghosting people, avoiding social media - this is my „battery saving mode” where I can hold onto that little amount of energy that I have instead of using it on interactions with others. I guess it’s one of typical introvert behaviors, but who knows?
.
I promise that I’m not dissapearing. I just need to focus on what matters the most. I’ll be back sooner or later with a new energy! Untill then - take care guyz 🌿 thank you for all your comments and messages, they always bring me smile

node.text: Bloom. // last week I was working a lot and I couldn’t find time and space for posting new drawings... this one is from last month! You might already seen a w.i.p. at my instastory or full picture with other color variants on my Patreon (patreon.com/Fuki) // I’m getting closer to moving to a new flat! 🙀 which is not yet done because there were lot of delays with renovations (I might show you how it looks like on Thursday if you want!). I already have a sofa but have no floor. I’m not sure if kitchen furnitures will be made on time. There’s 2 weeks till moving day and my new flat look far far away from being done 🙃So yeah, I’m stressed about that. But also I started to browse my clothes, books and stuff to sort it out, make a room sale (like a garage sale but I don’t have a garage). Then pack all the stuff into boxes. Hope that all renovations will be done on time. Move to a new flat. Start to unpack everything... It’s stressing me out a bit. And in the meantime I’ll be working almost every day so I won’t have much time to take a rest 🥲 I just hope it will be over soon. Cross your fingers for me! 🤞
